# Git Commit Rules

## Co-authorship — strictly forbidden

NEVER add any of the following to commit messages:
- `Co-authored-by: ...`
- `Co-authored-by: Claude <...>`
- `Co-authored-by: GitHub Copilot <...>`
- Any AI attribution line of any kind

Every commit must be authored solely by Prabhat. No exceptions.

## Commit message format

- Concise subject line (50 chars max)
- Focus on the "why", not the "what"
- No period at end of subject line
- Body optional, separated by a blank line if used

## Example

```
Add trafilatura fallback chain for sparse content
```

Not:
```
Add trafilatura fallback chain for sparse content

Co-authored-by: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
```
